  "prompt": "What are the alternatives to WalkMe?",
  "response": "There are several alternatives to WalkMe, each offering various features for digital adoption, user onboarding, and employee training. Some of the prominent options include:\n\n1. **Pendo**: Known for its product analytics and user guidance features, Pendo helps improve user engagement and onboarding.\n\n2. **Whatfix**: Provides in-app guidance and performance support for employees and customers, with features like interactive walkthroughs and tooltips.\n\n3. **Appcues**: Focuses on user onboarding and engagement, offering tools to create custom flows, tooltips, and modals without coding.\n\n4. **Userlane**: Offers a platform for interactive guides and onboarding, aiming to reduce training time and improve user proficiency.\n\n5. **Apty**: Provides digital adoption solutions with features like in-app guidance, analytics, and compliance tracking.\n\n6. **Guided**: Offers personalized onboarding and training solutions with interactive guides and user engagement tools.\n\n7. **Chameleon**: Specializes in product tours and user onboarding, allowing customization and integration with other analytics tools.\n\n8. **Tour My App**: A simpler tool for creating interactive tours and onboarding experiences within applications.\n\n9. **Intercom**: While primarily a customer messaging platform, Intercom offers features for onboarding and user engagement through targeted messages and product tours.\n\n10. **Inline Manual**: Provides interactive walkthroughs and tutorials to help users understand and use software applications effectively.\n\nEach of these platforms has its unique strengths and may be suited to different types of businesses and user needs.",
